events.flavourText: Your first impression is wind. Howling wind fills your eyes and ears, and you are nearly knocked from your feet by swirling blasts. You steady yourself and look around. This seems to be a windswept mountain top. Jagged rocks are piled around you, and white clouds race overhead in a dark blue sky. The air is thin, cold, and cruel.

script.name: Tornado Mountain to Ruins Of Hail

scripts.text:
Some text has been crudely carved into the wall here...

"Dorian here Slew the dragon Brontes, single handed. Think of me as ye Pass by traveller, and look for me Beyond the Gate."

events.flavourText: The cave smells musty and dry, and is heaped with bones of all descriptions. It appears deserted at first glance...
